whatly (6.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Performance & Privacy settings: GPU, process-model, JS-heap and HTTP-cache
    controls, plus a WebRTC IP-leak shield.
  * Network proxy (System/None/SOCKS5/HTTP), start-at-login, interface scale,
    and an optional custom (frameless) window frame.
  * Portal-based notifications for Flatpak, selectable per delivery backend.
  * Custom JavaScript addons (sandboxed); custom CSS and addons stored per
    account.
  * Grid view for multiple in-window accounts, alongside tabs and windows.
  * First-run setup wizard, and an optional custom window frame. See CHANGELOG.md.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix a crash opening the automatic-theme setup with no geolocation backend.
  * Quit gracefully on SIGTERM; stop echoing Qt WebEngine teardown noise.
  * Restore the About dialog's button icons.
  * Add a unit-test suite and integration coverage. See CHANGELOG.md.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Sat, 19 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Taskbar unread badge (Unity LauncherEntry), adjustable interface font size,
    optional auto-reload after a page crash, network status in the tray tooltip.
  * HiDPI: QT_SCALE_FACTOR scales the web content; WHATLY_MAX_FPS lifts the FPS
    cap. Build a dictionary subset with -DWHATLY_DICTIONARIES.
  * Optional Windows code signing via SignPath Foundation.
  * See CHANGELOG.md for the full list.

 -- Ángel Guzmán Maeso <angel@guzmanmaeso.com>  Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

whatly (6.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Native notifications now use a high-resolution app icon, so the logo no
    longer looks blurry on desktops with large notification popups such as
    Cinnamon on Linux Mint (issue #2).
  * See CHANGELOG.md for the full list.

